 its even easier. + they slow/haste/mez !<br /><br />Thats a typical group.  If you have a group that remotely looks like that. And your having "risk" in your grouping... Then those people have no business being there.  I cannot remember the last time i died grouping there.  I can count the # of times we had a wipe on one hand, in 3 levels, 16 AA's there.  Usually thats on a named, where we misjudged our DPS, or Tank got Random Wing boss proc 3 or 4 times in a row.<br /><br />Seriously, join a non-gimp group sometime, you will be amazed at how effortless it is.  There is NO risk.  <br /><br />Don't get me wrong I'm not even remotely uber, which is why this is just screwed up.  I have 1850hps SELF BUFFED.  I have died 2 POSSIBLY 3 times between 62-65 with 16 AA's. In BoT groups.  Usually its my OWN fault, or we had a War tank (sorry Wars, I love ya, but aggros rough with ya, even after FD'ing.)<br /><br />I really don't consider solo "risky".  Thats not the point.  The point is, its solo. <br /><br />I honestly can't believe people are saying, grouping is "high risk".  You guys must get the worste groups in the damn zone.  Tanks who don't know taunt, clerics who cast quick heal 5 times a pull on the tank.<br /><br />Absolutely mind boggling.  <br /><br />The point is, when your solo, you should be rewarded for killing high level mobs SOLO.  There is by far more effort employed solo then in a group.  <br /><br />With 1850hp self buffed, and all that time spent in that zone, your gonna tell me theres risk in grouping? To be honest I probably havn't died since 62 or early 63.  GROUPING.  Even then it was RARE and due to my mistake. (not re-upping FS after FD'ing and RE-FD'ing due to FS's aggro BEFORE sitting.  Then either random stun on me/unslowed mob, or WAR tank who can't get it off instantly like pals/sk's can.)<br /><br />So lets please talk about risk, bottom # of AA's, bottom # of hps and little to NO risk EVER.  Might as well be fighting Gnolls in JPF with how fast the damn Giants drop in good groups.  Seriously, its a joke.<br /><br />Edit - I know you've been to these zones but seriously by your descriptions, I can't beleive they are the same zones.  Or you just have the worste luck in the entire world when it comes to pick-up groups.  at least 4 out of 5 other people there know their class/roll.  The one who doesn't either catches on or gets bugged about what they are doing to the poitn that they leave. (yeah have fun, play the game as you want, but you dont get a mage for their melee capabilities with a random proc of 50 dmg weapon. Sorry you don't, when you do, its not the reason they were invited, or other such things absurd like that.)<br /></span></font></td>
